<compartment start="798" end="808" title="E2E guardrails test failure — subcommand dispatch stripped subcommand name" episode_type="bug,refactor" importance="72">
<p1>
E2E test `guardrails.spec.ts` was failing on CI: `guardrails list` and `guardrails policy` both returned "Unknown guardrail subcommand: (none)" because the CLI subcommand dispatch was calling `handleGuardrailsCommand([], io)` — it sliced off the subcommand name before passing `rest` to the handler, so `['list']` arrived as `[]` and no subcommand matched. Fix: `rest.slice(1)` → `rest` in the dispatch, so `guardrails list` correctly passes `['list']` to `runGuardrailsCommand`. CLI unit tests (10/10) passed before commit. Pushed as `52e48c78`.

U: "14issues 18min effort packages/memory/src/cortexkit/dreamer-consumer.test.ts ..."
</p1>
